added core and interrupt tolerances as optional parameters to the model function  by default the tolerances are set to infinity turning them off (+2 squashed commits) Squashed commits: [2f75de7] added new criterion core tolerance and interrupt tolerance to main  added additional enlargement option for use when the returned object is a Reaction [84b7bbd] Added additional option to the model function to set the tolerances for the new criterion

added in production and consumption calculations added in production and consumption calculations to liquid reactor (+2 squashed commits) Squashed commits: [1c427c9] syntax fixes [2174430] added missing comma (+3 squashed commits) Squashed commits: [b0d3123] Calculation of production and consumption rates added (+1 squashed commit) Squashed commits: [1232050] updated logRates header [0a48db8] added and initialized core production and consumption rates as fields of ReactionSystem  calculation of criterion  criterion related information added to logRates [40510f7] added arrays to store core production and consumption rates and tweaked the simulate function header to add the tolerances for the new criterion

added catch for dealing with zero consumption or production rates  if the concentration is zero the accumulation number for that species is left out of the total reaction accumulation number calculation  otherwise the analysis is terminated and the greatest flux production/consumption (as appropriate) reaction for that species is added to the model (+1 squashed commit) Squashed commits: [dd3b1ff] tweaks to handling the case when a Reaction object is returned for enlargement rather than a species object

Provides an ignoreOverallFluxCriterion boolean option  this option deactivates movement to core of a species based on its dimensionless flux  the toleranceMoveToCore then only applies to pressure dependent network exploration.  This allows pressure dependent models to be built using the new criterion only while still using the original tolerance to decide when to explore.
